    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>pasta </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> along with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>pasta </strong>for 7-9 min (10-12 min for wholewheat) or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>pasta</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/courgette-pea-and-goats-cheese-linguine/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top, tail and cut your <strong>courgette[s]</strong> into quarters lengthways, then into batons</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/courgette-pea-and-goats-cheese-linguine/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> and <strong>soft cheese </strong>in 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[170ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>creamy veg stock</strong></p><p>Peel and slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/courgette-pea-and-goats-cheese-linguine/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> sliced garlic</strong>, <strong>courgette batons </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until starting to soften</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/courgette-pea-and-goats-cheese-linguine/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, strip your <strong>mint leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them roughly, discard the stems</p><p>Add your<strong> blanched peas</strong> to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over them to refresh them</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/courgette-pea-and-goats-cheese-linguine/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the courgette has softened, add the <strong>cooked pasta </strong>and<strong> creamy veg stock </strong>to the pan and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Squeeze in the juice of <strong>half</strong> your<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>lemon[s] </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/courgette-pea-and-goats-cheese-linguine/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Remove from the heat and stir through <strong>half</strong> your <strong>goats' cheese</strong>, <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>mint </strong>(you'll use the rest for garnish!) and the <strong>refreshed peas </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>courgette, pea & goats' cheese pasta</strong></p><p>Wash your<strong> salad</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/courgette-pea-and-goats-cheese-linguine/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>courgette, pea & goats' cheese linguine</strong> and crumble over the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>goats' cheese</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>salad </strong>to the side and season with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>mint</strong>, <strong>lemon wedge </strong>and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
